---
description: Use Deno instead of Node.js, npm, pnpm, or vite.
globs: "*.ts, *.tsx, *.html, *.css, *.js, *.jsx, package.json"
alwaysApply: false
---

Default to using Deno instead of Node.js.

- Use `deno <file>` instead of `node <file>` or `ts-node <file>`
- Use `deno test` instead of `jest` or `vitest`
- Use `deno build <file.html|file.ts|file.css>` instead of `webpack` or `esbuild`
- Use `deno install` instead of `npm install` or `yarn install` or `pnpm install`
- Use `deno run <script>` instead of `npm run <script>` or `yarn run <script>` or `pnpm run <script>`
- Use `deno fmt` instead of `prettier`
- Use `deno lint` instead of `eslint`
- Use `deno check` instead of `tsc`
